message.entry: The DataType argument is ignored when code is not generated. The data type specified in the message is used to read the point cloud data.
Unable to store field {0} in point cloud message. Available fields are: {1}.
Field type {0} is not supported. Possible field types are: {1}.
Field type {0,number,integer} is not supported. Possible field types are: {1}.
Value of the "Parent" name-value argument must be a scalar graphics Axes handle. Modify the input accordingly.
Point cloud does not contain RGB color data.
Missing X, Y, or Z coordinate information in point cloud.
Field type of X, Y, or Z is not supported. Field type value must be between 1 and 8, and X, Y, and Z datatype must be the same size.
Size of RGB datatype must be at least 4 bytes.
Invalid PointCloud message type for this operation.
Error in reading the point cloud message.
Invalid message type for function "{0}". The "{0}" function supports only "{1}" as input message argument.
Expected input 'xyzPoints' must be of size M-by-3 or M-by-N-by-3.
Expected input 'rgb' must be of size M-by-3 or M-by-N-by-3.
Expected input 'intensity' must be a M-by-1 vector or M-by-N matrix.
Expected input 'rgb' dimensions must correspond to the number of available X,Y,Z points
Expected input 'intensity' dimensions must correspond to the number of available X,Y,Z points.
The data type for the color data of the PointCloud2 message differs from the data type specified in the call to rosReadRGB.
